## Disable TLS Certificate Validation for Current PowerShell Session

```powershell
$env:NODE_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED="0"
```

What:
Sets a Node.js environment variable for the current PowerShell session to ignore TLS/SSL certificate validation.

Why:
This can temporarily bypass certificate errors in restricted corporate networks or test environments.

When:
Use only for local troubleshooting when Node/npm requests fail because of certificate validation.

Warning:
This makes HTTPS connections less secure. Do not use it permanently or in production.

---

## Disable npm Strict SSL

```powershell
npm config set strict-ssl false
```

What:
Tells npm not to strictly validate SSL certificates.

Why:
It can help npm install packages behind corporate proxies or SSL-inspection networks.

When:
Use only if npm install fails because of SSL certificate errors and your network requires this workaround.

Warning:
This reduces package download security. Prefer fixing the proper corporate certificate/proxy configuration when possible.

